{
  "stem": "20609.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This is a country which produces an abundance of food, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, the-- the kids in-- in school, the kids in a city like Copenhagen or Odense or wherever the big cities was had to be like every summer during their vacation there, farmers took in two or three kids so they can feed those kids.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That's how-- I know we had three at my farm.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had three sisters from Copenhagen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I even know their name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] I was so in love with one of them, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] They came from very rich people then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The-- the one-- the older sister was called Ose.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Ose.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the second sister was-- no, it was Birthe, Birthe, B-I-R-T-H-E, Hanne Jenssen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They always have like two names, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I found out after the war that the-- the-- the father was a General Motors distributor.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He handled Chevrolets, trucks, and Opel cars.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So they were from a rich family, but they didn't have nothing to eat, you know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So every year these kids came to that farm, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And we-- [LAUGHS] I was just looking forward to it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Again, I was too young to appreciate it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "So-- but we worked very, very hard, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, we lost our teacher in 1941.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "He received his permission to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And the only way he could go to Russia.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He went to Russia.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "That was before the Germans' march.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I think it was '40 or '41.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I'm not sure the exact-- all of a sudden, we had no more school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And that meant now we were like seven days a week.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
